article.description: Hunter Janacek hit six 3-pointers and scored a career-high 22 points as Lafayette snapped a short two-game losing skid with a 104-67 win over Moravian College on Monday night.
article.headline: Janacek's career-best 22 powers Lafayette
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- Hunter Janacek hit six 3-pointers and scored a career-high 22 points as Lafayette snapped a short two-game losing skid with a 104-67 win over Moravian College on Monday night. Janacek made 7 of 13 field goals overall and added five rebounds. Eric Stafford and Kyle Stout each finished with 17 points for Lafayette (4-6), which topped the 100-point mark for the first time since 2008. Overall the Leopards hit 53.7 percent of their shots and 14 of 28 from long range. O'Neil Holder scored 14 to lead the Greyhounds, who were held to just 31 percent shooting and turned it over 20 times. Lafayette led by 11 at the half and blew the game open midway through the second. Myles Cherry hit a jumper for a 70-50 Leopards lead with 10:57 left, and a Stout 3 about three minutes later pushed the lead past 30 to 85-54.
